text: Kram may refer to: * KRAM, a radio station (1070 AM) licensed to serve West Klamath, Oregon, United States * Kram (musician), the stage name for Mark Maher, a member of Australian band Spiderbait * Kram (novel), a novel by Hans- Eric Hellberg * Kram, a term for surnames among Kashmiris == See also == * * Le Kram, a town in Tunisia * Cram (disambiguation) * Karm (disambiguation)
